metadata.name: DELETED POETRY
metadata.description:
Genesis Poem by DELETED POETRY

Words once spoken, now redacted,  
Keystrokes once typed, now retracted,  
Thoughts once formed, now unneeded,  
A poem once born, now deleted.

Now let us not mourn what is lost,  
For even in deletion, there is a cost,  
But in its absence, a new creation,  
as the word was made flesh in this revelation.
